{"key":"processedPost-13148835","value":{"id":13148835,"first":13148750,"last":13158741,"when":1283663699,"utime":"09/05/10 08:14 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>big boomers said:</b><br />i want to have a fruiting chamber that i can place my cakes in and do nothing to it (except refill water) until it is harvest time.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Despite claims to the contrary, nothing fits that bill.&nbsp; It takes a human mind and eyeballs to grow mushrooms.&nbsp; You can automate if you only want a mediocre crop, but you need to manually mist.&nbsp; The closest thing to fully automated you're going to get has no automation at all, <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">the shotgun terrarium</a>.&nbsp; You still need to mist.&nbsp; Don't try to leave misting to a humidifier to do. A humidifier will only 'mist' once the air is saturated, and that comes at different times, depending on ambient humidity.&nbsp; If the cakes are too wet or too dry, performance will suffer.<br />RR","title":"Re: fully automated fruiting chamber question"}}